account for important known differences. Since worksharing
activities reduce <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">United States</ENAMEX> costs by <NUMEX TYPE="PERCENT">about 25 percent</NUMEX> (<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Cohen et</ENAMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="CONTACT_INFO">al. 2001</ENAMEX>), we increase model costs to account for the lack of
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">worksharing</ENAMEX> in <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Italy</ENAMEX>. The portion of the model costs that are labor
